You are rebuilding the website for Alta Strada Consulting, Inc. — a medical device sales consulting firm representing biologics and hardware companies to orthopedic surgeons, podiatrists, and neurosurgeons.

This is a COMPLETE visual redesign. The old dark/navy design was too bland. The new design is: white/light base, blue accents from the logo, real animations, visual depth, modern and polished. Think premium consulting firm, not hospital website.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ App Router, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion for animations (staggered reveals, scroll animations, hover effects, counters)
- React Hook Form for contact form
- next/font/google for typography, next/image for all images
- Server components by default. "use client" only when needed.

## Color Palette (from the logo)
--blue-primary: #1E6FC4 (main accent — buttons, links, highlights)
--blue-dark: #0D3B7A (deep navy — header text, footer bg)
--blue-deeper: #091F48 (darkest — footer)
--blue-light: #3A8FE2 (hover states)
--blue-pale: #E8F1FB (card backgrounds, subtle sections)
--blue-wash: #F2F7FD (faint blue alternating section bg)
--white: #FFFFFF
--off-white: #FAFBFD (page bg)
--gray-50: #F5F7FA
--gray-100: #E9ECF1 (borders)
--gray-400: #8896A6 (muted text)
--gray-600: #4A5568 (body text)
--gray-800: #1E293B (headings)

White base. Blue accent. No neon, no gradients on buttons, no dark theme (only footer + stats bar are dark).

## Typography
- Headings: DM Serif Display (serif, authoritative)
- Body/UI: DM Sans (clean sans-serif)
- Never use Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system fonts.
- Every section has a small uppercase label above the heading: text-sm, tracking-wide, uppercase, text-blue-primary, font-semibold.

## Animation Rules (Framer Motion — USE EXTENSIVELY)
- Every section fades + slides up on scroll (whileInView, viewport once)
- Card grids use staggered children (staggerChildren: 0.12)
- All cards have hover: scale(1.02), shadow deepens, translateY(-4px)
- Buttons: hover darkens bg, subtle lift
- Stats section: animated counters that count up on scroll
- Hero: staggered entrance (label → heading → text → button, 150ms delay each)
- Nav: transparent → solid white + shadow on scroll (0.3s transition)
- Hero scroll indicator: small bouncing chevron at bottom
- Import shared variants from lib/animations.ts — do NOT define inline everywhere
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Layout Rules
- Max 1200px content width, centered
- 96px section padding desktop, 64px mobile
- Generous whitespace
- Section backgrounds alternate: white → blue-wash/gray-50 → white
- Use subtle curved SVG dividers between at least 2-3 sections
- Thin 3-4px blue gradient line at very top of page above nav
- Cards: rounded-lg, shadow-sm default, shadow-lg on hover, never flat

## Logo
- Navbar: Icon mark (A) at 40px + "ALTA STRADA" as styled text in blue-dark
- Footer: Full logo on dark background
- Favicon: Just the A icon mark

## Pages: Home, About, Portfolio, Specialties, Contact
See the full redesign prompt document for detailed page-by-page layouts.

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict — no `any`
- Functional components with explicit prop types
- cn() utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Tailwind only — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Semantic HTML (section, nav, main, header, footer — not divs for everything)
- All images have alt text, all interactive elements have focus states
- Content lives in lib/constants.ts, animation variants in lib/animations.ts

## NEVER
- Stock medical photos (no stethoscopes, handshakes, smiling nurses)
- Pricing, SKUs, or proprietary manufacturer info
- Carousels, sliders, chatbots, pop-ups
- Dark theme for main content (only footer + stats bar)
- Flat cards with no hover states
- Static, lifeless sections with no scroll animation
- SaaS / startup aesthetic
- Lorem ipsum